data.title: Hollingworth: time to end debate and take firm action
data.meta_description: Andrew Bartlett, leader of the Australian Democrats, says the Governor-General, Peter Hollingworth, must resign or be sacked. But Terry O'Gorman , president of the Australian Council for Civil Liberties , says he should not resign because of a media and public opinion witch-hunt.
